rm.com/political/toronto-ward-18-candidate-review|title=Toronto Ward 18 Candidate Review|last=NP|first=Neil|website=www.choicestorm.com|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-04-19}}</ref> Endorsed by the [[Toronto Star]]<ref name=\":5\" /> and [[Now (newspaper)|Now Magazine]].<ref name=\":6\" /> \n|-\n| Mohammed Uddin|| 540 ||2.81\n|02-Jan-14\n|\n|-\n| Jolene Hunt|| 358 ||1.86\n|28-Feb-14\n|\n|-\n| Paul Alves|| 274 ||1.43\n|08-Jul-14\n|\n|-\n| Elsa Romao|| 270 ||1.41\n|18-Feb-14\n|\n|-\n| Jim McMillan|| 213 ||1.11\n|30-Jun-14\n|\n|-\n| Derek Power|| 198 ||1.03\n|09-Jul-14\n|\n|-\n| Bobby Beckett|| 182 ||0.95\n|11-Sep-14\n|\n|-\n| Joseph Ferrari|| 176 ||0.92\n|03-Jan-14\n|\n|-\n| Robert Rodrigues|| 131 ||0.68\n|05-Sep-14\n|\n|-\n| Dennis Pavao|| 76 ||0.40\n|11-Sep-14\n|\n|-\n! Total|| 19,207 ||100\n!\n!\n|}\n\n===Ward 19 - Trinity\u2014Spadina===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 150px;\" | Candidate Name\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 100px;\" | Number of votes\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 100px;\" | % of votes\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 100px;\" | Nomination Date\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 500px;\" | Biography and policies\n|-\n| '''[[Mike Layton]]'''|| 21,014 ||83.66\n|08-Jul-14\n|Son of the late NDP Leader and former Toronto City Councillor [[Jack Layton]]. Stepson of mayoral candidate [[Olivia Chow]]. Incumbent of Toronto City Council since 2010. Resident of Trinity-Spadina for over 25 years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www1.toronto.ca/wps/portal/contentonly?vgnextoid=3e793293dc3ef310VgnVCM10000071d60f89RCRD&vgnextchannel=c3a83293dc3ef310VgnVCM10000071d60f89RCRD|title=Councillor Mike Layton - Council Members - Council Members {{!}} City of Toronto|language=en-CA|access-date=2017-04-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170413154350/http://www1.toronto.ca/wps/portal/contentonly?vgnextoid=3e793293dc3ef310VgnVCM10000071d60f89RCRD&vgnextchannel=c3a83293dc3ef310VgnVCM10000071d60f89RCRD|archive-date=2017-04-13|url-status=dead}}</