170407054516/http://www1.toronto.ca/wps/portal/contentonly?vgnextoid=6b493293dc3ef310VgnVCM10000071d60f89RCRD|archive-date=2017-04-07|url-status=dead}}</ref> Campaign issues included expansion of the subway system and eliminating the land transfer tax.<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.insidetoronto.com/news-story/4921070-ward-24-debate-gets-heated-as-willowdale-candidates-square-off/|title=WARD 24: Debate gets heated as Willowdale candidates square off|last=InsideToronto.com|website=www.insidetoronto.com|access-date=2017-04-06}}</ref>\n|-\n| Dan Fox|| 5,649 ||29.08\n|28-Feb-14\n|Community volunteer and public servant, has worked in both public and private sectors.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.insidetoronto.com/news-story/4868796-dan-fox/|title=Dan Fox|last=InsideToronto.com|website=www.insidetoronto.com|access-date=2017-04-06}}</ref> Campaign issues included reducing traffic congestion, improving transit infrastructure, expanding parks.<ref name=\":10\" /> Endorsed by the [[Toronto Star]],<ref name=\":5\" /> former Education Minister [[Gerard Kennedy]], [[Now (newspaper)|Now Magazine]]<ref name=\":6\" /> and [[Toronto & York Region Labour Council]].<ref name=\":8\" /> \n|-\n| Randy Ai|| 1,299 ||6.69\n|13-Aug-14\n|Lawyer. Campaign issues included freezing property taxes for the next term of council, eliminating the land transfer tax and traffic congestion.<ref name=\":10\" />\n|-\n| Michael Galea|| 1,098 ||5.65\n|23-Jul-14\n|Willowdale resident of 33 years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.insidetoronto.com/news-story/4861222-michael-galea/|title=Michael Galea|last=InsideToronto.com|website=www.insidetoronto.com|access-date=2017-04-06}}</ref> Architectural designer and community planner. Campaign issues included public transit, inclusive community planning and better fiscal management of capital projects in the city.<ref name=\":10\" />\n|-\n| Daniela Acerra|| 661 ||3.40\n|12-Sep-14\n|\n|-\n! Total|| 19,423 ||100\n!\n!\n|}\n\n===Ward 25 - Don Valley West===\n