al||align=right| 12,298 ||align=right| 100% \n|}\n\n*'''Gianfranco Amendola''' (registered July 9)\n*'''[[Maria Augimeri]]''' ''elected''<ref name=\"cbc\"/> (incumbent) (registered March 11) First elected to North York City Council in 1985 and then to the new Toronto City Council in 1997. A social anthropologist by training.\n*'''Wilson Basante''' (registered January 4)\n*'''Gus Cusimano''' (registered August 25)\n*'''Stefano Picone''' (registered August 26)\n\n==Ward 10: York Centre==\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"8\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|Colspan=\"3\" align=\"center\"|'''Ward 10''' \n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"150px\" | Candidate\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\"  | Votes\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\"  | %\n|-\n|'''[[James Pasternak]]''' ||align=right| 3,159 ||align=right| 19.156% \n|-\n|Nancy Oomen ||align=right| 2,777 ||align=right| 16.839% \n|-\n|Brian Shifman ||align=right| 2,632 ||align=right| 15.96% \n|-\n|Igor Toutchinski ||align=right| 2,605 ||align=right| 15.796% \n|-\n|Konstantin Toubis ||align=right| 1,887 ||align=right| 11.443% \n|-\n|Magda Gondor Berkovits ||align=right| 935 ||align=right| 5.67% \n|-\n|Jarred Friedman ||align=right| 850 ||align=right| 5.154% \n|-\n|Joseph Cohen ||align=right| 535 ||align=right| 3.244% \n|-\n|Eric Plant ||align=right| 355 ||align=right| 2.153% \n|-\n|Edward Zaretsky ||align=right| 326 ||align=right| 1.977% \n|-\n|Robert Freedland ||align=right| 244 ||align=right| 1.48% \n|-\n|Drago Banovic ||align=right| 186 ||align=right| 1.128% \n|-\n!Total||align=right| 16,491 ||align=right| 100% \n|}\n\nIncumbent [[Mike Feldman]] did not run for re-election.\n\n*'''Drago Banovic''' (registered September 9)\n*'''Joseph Cohen''' (registered August 23)\n*'''Robert Freedland''' (registered September 9)\n*'''Jarred Friedman''' (registered July 29)\n*'''Magda Gondor Berkovits''' (registered January 4) Gondor Berkovits managed the constituency office of a federal Member of Parliament before becoming a businessperson. A former