cil |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-01-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110927153538/http://www.sharenews.com/local-news/2010/09/22/ctv%E2%80%99s-karlene-nation-running-city-council |archivedate=2011-09-27 }}</ref>\n*'''George Sawision''' (registered June 14)\n*'''Jason Stevens''' (registered June 28)\n*'''Karen Sun''' (registered January 4) Sun has been executive director of the [[Chinese Canadian National Council]] Toronto Chapter since 2006<ref name=eyew/><ref name=globejan5>[https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/rossi-first-to-jump-into-race-to-replace-miller/article1419060/ \"Rossi first to jump into race to replace Miller\"], ''The Globe and Mail'', January 5, 2010</ref> and was on \"Better Ballots\"' list of candidates to watch. She has sat on the boards of Heritage Toronto and the Working Women Community Centre.<ref name=nowcand/> She was endorsed by [[Judy Rebick]], ''[[Spacing Magazine]]'' co-founder [[David Meslin]], Tam Goossen, Winnie Ng, former Ward 19 candidate Derek Chadbourne, [[Darren O'Donnell]], Kathryn Holloway and [[Wavelength Music Arts Projects]] co-founder Jonny Dovercourt.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.karensun.ca/?page_id=75 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-01-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110901204458/http://www.karensun.ca/?page_id=75 |archivedate=2011-09-01 }}</ref> She was also endorsed by the [[Toronto Star]].<ref>{{cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.thestar.com/article/876714--star-election-choices-for-city-council#comments|title=The Star's choices for Toronto council, Wards 1-21|date=|work=The Star|access-date=|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180912131500/https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2010/10/18/the_stars_choices_for_toronto_council_wards_121.html|archive-date=September 12, 2018|location=Toronto}}</ref>\n\n==Ward 20: Trinity\u2014Spadina==\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"8\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|Col