/>\n*'''[[Jane Pitfield]]''' (registered January 6) Pitfield is a former city councillor for Ward 26 (Don Valley West) and ran for mayor in 2006 as a right of centre candidate, losing to David Miller. She is associated with the provincial Progressive Conservatives and was endorsed by retiring city councillor Case Ootes.<ref name=nowcand/>\n*'''Mike Restivo''' (registered January 18)\n*'''John Richardson''' (registered January 22)\n*'''Jennifer Wood''' (registered February 12)\n\n==Ward 30: Toronto\u2014Danforth==\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"8\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|Colspan=\"3\" align=\"center\"|'''Ward 30''' \n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"150px\" | Candidate\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\"  | Votes\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\"  | %\n|-\n|'''[[Paula Fletcher]]''' ||align=right| 8,766 ||align=right| 45.356% \n|-\n|Liz West ||align=right| 8,507 ||align=right| 44.016% \n|-\n|Andrew James ||align=right| 620 ||align=right| 3.208% \n|-\n|Mark Dewdney ||align=right| 518 ||align=right| 2.68% \n|-\n|Mihaly Varga ||align=right| 313 ||align=right| 1.619% \n|-\n|Angie Tingas ||align=right| 262 ||align=right| 1.356% \n|-\n|Andreas Bogojevic ||align=right| 198 ||align=right| 1.024% \n|-\n|Gary Walsh ||align=right| 143 ||align=right| 0.74% \n|-\n!Total||align=right| 19,327 ||align=right| 100% \n|}\n\n*'''Andreas Bogojevic''' (registered September 3)\n*'''Mark Dewdney''' (registered March 9)\n*'''[[Paula Fletcher]]''' ''elected''<ref name=\"cbc\"/> (incumbent) - former leader of the [[Manitoba Communist Party]]; won election to third term;<ref>Richard Warnica, [http://news.nationalpost.com/toronto/wards-to-watch-toronto-danforth-mainstay-paula-fletcher-faces-opponents-right-left-and-centre Wards to watch: Toronto-Danforth mainstay Paula Fletcher faces opponents right, left and centre] (October 8, 2014).</ref> chair of Parks and Environment Committee (2006-2010), piloting the city's climate change strategy<ref>[https://www.assocsrv.ca/cpsa-acsp/2015event/Schwartz.pdf