ra.ca/public/National/Gladstone_to_run_for_Toronto_city_council-9084.aspx \"Gladstone to run for Toronto city council\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20130115195606/http://www.xtra.ca/public/National/Gladstone_to_run_for_Toronto_city_council-9084.aspx |date=2013-01-15 }}, ''Xtra'', August 24, 2010</ref> He is also campaigning against the Tuggs contract.<ref>[https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/toronto/city-votes/mug-full-of-frustration-spills-at-boardwalk-pub/article1704755/ \"Mug full of frustration spills at Boardwalk Pub\"], ''The Globe and Mail'', September 12, 2010</ref> Gladstone dropped out of the race and threw his support behind fellow candidate Mary-Margaret McMahon<ref name=\"thestar.com\">{{cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/elections/article/876321--john-tory-endorses-bussin-rival|title=John Tory endorses Bussin rival|date=|work=The Star|access-date=|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200212144234/https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2010/10/15/john_tory_endorses_bussin_rival.html|archive-date=February 12, 2020|location=Toronto}}</ref>\n*'''[[Mary-Margaret McMahon]]''' ''elected''<ref name=\"cbc\"/> (registered May 13) McMahon received former Ontario PC Party Leader [[John Tory]]'s endorsement on Saturday, October 16.<ref name=\"thestar.com\"/>\n*'''Kieron Pope''' (registered May 12)\n*'''Neil Sinclair''' (registered August 30)Retired lawyer and businessman who also dropped out of the race and threw his support behind Mary-Margaret McMahon\n\n==Ward 33: Don Valley East==\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"8\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|Colspan=\"3\" align=\"center\"|'''Ward 33''' \n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"150px\" | Candidate\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\"  | Votes\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\"  | %\n|-\n|'''[[Shelley Carroll]]''' ||align=right| 7,946 ||align=right| 57.659% \n|-\n|Fil Giannakopoulos ||align=right| 2,787 ||align=right| 20.223% \n|-\n|Mike Ihnat ||align=right| 1,886 ||align=r