oducer Chris Hughes\n| note2           = 2005\n| length2         = 35:00\n| title3          = The Way You Are\n| note3           = music video\n| length3         = 3:57\n| title4          = Mothers Talk\n| note4           = alternate UK video\n| length4         = 4:00\n| title5          = Mothers Talk\n| note5           = music video\n| length5         = 4:49\n| title6          = Shout\n| note6           = music video\n| length6         = 6:31\n| title7          = Everybody Wants to Rule the World\n| note7           = music video\n| length7         = 4:52\n| title8          = Head over Heels\n| note8           = music video\n| length8         = 4:26\n| title9          = I Believe\n| note9           = music video\n| length9         = 4:45\n| title10         = Mothers Talk\n| note10          = U.S. remix) (music video\n| length10        = 4:52\n| title11         = Everybody Wants to Run the World\n| note11          = music video\n| length11        = 4:52\n| title12         = The Way You Are\n| note12          = ''[[Top of the Pops]]''\n| length12        = 4:11\n| title13         = Mothers Talk\n| note13          = ''Top of the Pops''\n| length13        = 3:48\n| title14         = Mothers Talk\n| note14          = ''Top of the Pops''\n| length14        = 3:51\n| title15         = Shout\n| note15          = ''Top of the Pops''\n| length15        = 4:20\n| title16         = Everybody Wants to Rule the World\n| note16          = ''[[Wogan]]''\n| length16        = 4:08\n| title17         = Everybody Wants to Rule the World\n| note17          = ''Top of the Pops''\n| length17        = 3:35\n| title18         = Everybody Wants to Rule the World\n| note18          = ''Top of the Pops''\n| length18        = 3:45\n| title19         = The Working Hour\n| note19          = ''Wogan''\n| length19        = 4:28\n}}\n\n== Personnel ==\n===Tears for Fears===\n*[[Roland Orzabal]] \u2013 [[guitar]], [[Keyboard instrument|keyboards]], [[Lead vocalist|lead vocals]], [[grand piano]] on 5, vocal styling on 8, [[Keyboard bass|bass synth]] and [[LinnDrum]] [[Programming (music)|programming]] on 1\n*[[Curt Smith]] \u2013 [[bass guitar]], backing vocals, lead vocals on 3 and 8\n*[[Ian Stanley]] \u2013 [[Keyboard instrument|keyboards]], [[LinnDrum]] [[programming (music)|programming]], arrangements on \"Listen\"\n*[[Manny Elias]] \u2013 [[Drum kit|drums]] (all except track 1), drum arrangement on \"The Working Hour\"\n\n===Additional personnel===\n*\"Shout\": Sandy McLelland \u2013 [[Backing vocalist|backing vocals]], [[Chris Hughes (record producer)|Chris Hughes]] \u2013 drums\n*\"The Working Hour\": [[Jerry Marotta]] \u2013 percussion and saxophone arrangement, [[Will Gregory]] \u2013 [[saxophone]] solos, [[Mel Collins]] \u2013 [[saxophone]], Andy Davis \u2013 [[grand piano]]\n*\"Everybody Wants to Rule the World\": [[Neil Taylor (guitarist)|Neil Taylor]] \u2013 second [[guitar]] [[Guitar solo|solo]], [[Chris Hughes (record producer)|Chris Hughes]] - [[MIDI]] [[Programming (music)|programming]] [[Drumulator]]\n*\"Mothers Talk\": [[Stevie Vann|Stevie Lange]] \u2013 backing vocals\n*\"I Believe\": [[Will Gregory]] \u2013 saxophone\n*\"Broken\": [[Neil Taylor (guitarist)|Neil Taylor]] \u2013 guitar solo\n*\"Head Over Heels\": Sandy McLelland \u2013 backing vocals, [[Stackridge|Andy Davis]] \u2013 [[grand piano]], Annie McCaig \u2013 backing vocals, Marilyn Davis \u2013 backing vocals\n*\"Listen\": Marilyn Davis \u2013 [[opera]]tic vocal\n\n=== Production ===\n*[[Chris Hughes (record producer)|Chris Hughes]] \u2013 [[Record producer|producer]]\n*Dave Bascombe \u2013 [[Audio engineering|engineer]]\n*Paul King \u2013 [[Talent manager|management]]\n*Tim O'Sullivan \u2013 [[Photographer|cover photography]]\n\n== Charts and certifications ==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n=== Charts ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! Chart (1985)\n! Peak<br />position\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Australian Albums ([[Kent Music Report]])<ref>{{cite book|last=Kent|first=David|authorlink=David Kent (historian)|title=Australian Chart Book 1970\u20131992|publisher=Australian Chart Book|location=St. Ives, N.S.W.|year=1993|edition=Illustrated|page=306|isbn=0-646-11917-6}} N.B. the Kent Report chart was licensed by [[Australian Recording Industry Association|ARIA]] between mid 1983 and 19 June 1988.</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|5\n|-\n|{{albumchart |Austria |22 |artist=Tears for Fears |album=Songs from the Big Chair |accessdate=9 June 2014}}\n|-\n{{Albumchart |BillboardCanada |1 |M |title=''RPM'' 100 Albums, April 13, 1985 |url=http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?&file_num=nlc008388.0508&type=1&interval=36&PHPSESSID=c6btf3r8hs459qqt5ln3o3dcv5 |work=[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]], Vol. 42 No. 5 |publisher=Library and Archives Canada |location=Canada |accessdate=9 June 2014}}\n|-\n|{{albumchart |France |12 |artist=Tears for Fears |album=Songs from the Big Chair |accessdate=9 June 2014}}\n|-\n|{{albumchart |Germany |1 |M |title=Top 100 Longplay, 25 March 1985 |url=http://www.officialcharts.de/charts.asp?cat=a&country=de&year=1985&date=19850325&x=30&y=13 |work=Top 100 Longplay |publisher=[[Media Control]] |location=Germany |accessdate=9 June 2014}}\n|-\n|{{albumchart |Netherlands |1 |artist=Tears for Fears |album=Songs from the Big Chair |accessdate=9 June 2014}}\n|-\n|{{albumchart |New Zealand |2 |artist=Tears for Fears |album=Songs from the Big Chair |accessdate=9 June 2014}}\n|-\n|{{albumchart |Norway |17 |artist=Tears for Fears |album=Songs from the Big Chair |accessdate=9 June 2014}}\n|-\n|{{albumchart |Sweden |25 |artist=Tears for Fears |album=Songs from the Big Chair |accessdate=9 June 2014}}\n|-\n|{{albumchart |Switzerland |5 |artist=Tears for Fears |album=Songs from the Big Chair |accessdate=9 June 2014}}\n|-\n|{{albumchart |UK2 |2 |artist=Tears for Fears |album=Songs from the Big Chair |date=1985-03-09 |accessdate=9 June 2014}}\n|-\n|{{albumchart |Billboard200 |1 |M |title=''Billboard'' 200, retrieved f